<%@second_nav = track_second_nav('home')%>

<% content_for :title_bar do %>
    <div class="mac_ipad_preview">
    </div>
<%end-%>

<div class="outer_contaner" id="tour_features">
    <div class="inner_container" id="tour_features_inner">
        <h1 class="tool_title">Time Tracking Tool - Feature Tour</h1>
        
        <ul class="feature_list">
            <li class="pos_1">
                <h2 class="blue_med_oswald_text">Overview</h2>
                <p>FleetSuite’s employee time tracking software offers immediate and detailed insight into the progress of your active projects. Individual and team times are tracked against granular features and tasks, and compared to initial estimates for a clear overview of current performance, helping you rapidly identify bottlenecks and delays that require action.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pos_2">
                <h2 class="blue_med_oswald_text">Timesheets</h2>
                <p>All users can track their time via an intuitive calendar interface tailored to the specific working hours of your business, referencing both project tasks and internal tasks (such as vacations and breaks) for increased accuracy of reporting. Administrators have instant access to team activity and can edit tracking data as required to ensure an up-to-date view of progress.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pos_3">
                <h2 class="blue_med_oswald_text">Features & tasks</h2>
                <p>Break large projects into their component features to improve estimation and tracking capability. Discrete tasks can be assigned either to the overall project or to a specific feature, with teams and individuals tracking their progress against these tasks so you can easily account for every hour spent on a project.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pos_4">
                <h2 class="blue_med_oswald_text">Charts</h2>
                <p>All data submitted is automatically collated and displayed in a range of visual charts ideal for presenting project updates or retrospectives to stakeholders across the business. With task, team and individual contributions clearly displayed you have access to the objective, measurable data that enables you to effectively evolve and refine your processes.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pos_5">
                <h2 class="blue_med_oswald_text">Reporting</h2>
                <p>Submitted data from the employee time tracking software is available to administrators in the form of clear and usable reports, detailing start and end times for all tasks and dates. Delivering only the most relevant information for your business to increase the efficiency of human resources management is increased, you can co-ordinate even flexible working models with ease.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pos_6">
                <h2 class="blue_med_oswald_text">Schedule integration</h2>
                <p>FleetSuite’s uniquely modular online project collaboration tools mean that your time tracking capability can be seamlessly integrated with other functionality from across the suite and displayed in a central dashboard for immediate and central access. Compare tracked activities against those.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="clearing"></div>
        
        <div class="core_intro">
            <h1 class="core_title">Core features</h1>
            <p class="small_light_shadow_text">The core features included as standard with all FleetSuite accounts<br/> make managing multiple projects, teams and tools simple and intuitive.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="outer_contaner" id="core_features_select">
    <div class="inner_container" id="core_features_select_inner">
        <div class="core_expand"></div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="outer_contaner" id="core_features_content">
    <div class="inner_container" id="core_features_content_inner">
        <ul class="four_col_list">
            <li class="pos_1">
                <h2 class="blue_small_oswald_text">Dashboards</h2>
                <p>A visually engaging front page provides a high-level overview of all tasks and actions from across your chosen components.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pos_2">
                <h2 class="blue_small_oswald_text">Projects</h2>
                <p>Create, edit and archive projects to maintain an up-to-date overview of activity, with easy access to more granular information as required.  </p>
            </li>
            <li class="pos_3">
                <h2 class="blue_small_oswald_text">Teams & People</h2>
                <p>Create profiles for users across your business so they can easily view and understand their own schedules and tasks.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pos_4">
                <h2 class="blue_small_oswald_text">Clients</h2>
                <p>Connect distinct projects to specific clients for a joined-up view of your workload and added information for project teams.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="clearing"></div>
        
        <span class="signup_button">
            <%= link_to pricing_path(:from => 'track'), :class => 'pricing_and_signup_button' do %>
                See Pricing &amp; Signup
                <%= content_tag(:span, "30-Day Free Trial") %>
            <% end %>
        </span>
    </div>
</div>